In [17]:
def norm_data(df):
  x = df.copy()
  for i in x.columns[1:]:
    x[i] = x[i]/x[i][0]

  return x
In [18]:
def interactive_plot(df, title):
  fig = px.line(title = title)
  for i in df.columns[1:]:
    fig.add_scatter(x = df['Date'], y = df[i], name = i)
  fig.show()

def create_weights(seed=101):
  np.random.seed(seed)

  weights = np.array(np.random.random(9))
  return weights/weights.sum()

# Note that enumerate returns the value and a counter as well
# Assumption default is initial investment is $1 million

def calc_investment(df, w, initial_inv = 1000000):
  x = df.copy()
#  print(x.columns)
#  print()
  for i, stock in enumerate(x.columns):
    if i != 0:
#      print(i, stock)
      x[stock] = (x[stock] * w[i-1]) * initial_inv
 
  return x

In [34]:
def create_return_cols(df) :
  df['Portfolio Daily Worth In $'] = np.array(df.sum(axis=1))


  df['Portfolio daily % return'] = 0.0000

  for i in range(len(df)):
    if i != 0:
      df['Portfolio daily % return'][i] = ((df['Portfolio Daily Worth In $'][i]-df['Portfolio Daily Worth In $'][i-1])/df['Portfolio Daily Worth In $'][i-1]) * 100

  return df

CALCUATE PORTFOLIO ALLOCATION - DAILY RETURN/WORTH¶

In [36]:
# Lets assume we have $1,000,000 to be invested and we will allocate this fund based on the weights of the stocks
# We will create a function that takes in the stock prices along with the weights and return:
# (1) Daily value of each individual securuty in $ over the specified time period
# (2) Overall daily worth of the entire portfolio 
# (3) Daily return 


def portfolio_allocation(df, seed=101):

  df = create_return_cols(calc_investment(norm_data(df), w=create_weights(seed)))
  
  interactive_plot(df.drop(['Portfolio Daily Worth In $', 'Portfolio daily % return'], axis=1), 'Portfolio Individual Stocks Worth in $ Over Time')

  fig = px.line(x = df['Date'], y = df['Portfolio daily % return'], title = 'Portfolio Daily % Return')
  fig.show()

  fig = px.histogram(df, x = 'Portfolio daily % return', title = 'Histogram of Portfolio Daily % Return')
  fig.show()

  return df

def portfolio_overall_value(df, seed=101):

  df = create_return_cols(calc_investment(norm_data(df), w=create_weights(seed)))
  

  fig = px.line(x = df['Date'], y = df['Portfolio Daily Worth In $'] , title= 'Portfolio Overall Value in $ for seed: {}'.format(seed))
  fig.show()

  return df
